Article 7 ‚Äî Legal Basis

The University operates according to the laws of the Kyrgyz Republic and its own Charter, on the principles of autonomy and self-government. The state may intervene only in cases provided by law.
Management bodies: Founders, Supervisory Board, President, Academic Council, Rector, Audit Commission.

Article 8 ‚Äî General Meeting of Founders

This is the highest governing body.
Its powers include:

- creation/liquidation of the University and its subdivisions;
- approval of the Charter and amendments;
- appointment of the President and approval of the Rector;
- approval of financial plans, reports and budget;
- determination of management structure and key executives;
- approval of important orders and acts;
- any other important decisions not assigned to other bodies.
Decisions are binding for all and may be formalized by orders.

Article 9 ‚Äî Supervisory Board

Internal control body.
Consists of 3 people (chairman + 2 members).
Has the right to:

- conduct inspections, audits, obtain documentation;
- monitor the University's activities and compliance with the Charter;
- impose veto (through the founders).
Works on a voluntary basis. May be recalled early.

Article 10 ‚Äî University President

Sole executive head, responsible for organizational, financial and personnel policy.
Appointed by the founders, accountable to them.

His powers include:

- disposal of property within competence;
- implementation of founders' decisions and distribution of funds;
- issuance of orders;
- representation of the University without power of attorney;
- creation of branches, centers, subdivisions (with consent of founders);
- participation in the work of the Academic Council;
- approval of budget, reports, financial documents;
- international representation;
- development of internal regulations;
- preparation of proposals for reorganization and development of the University.

Grounds for termination of powers - decision of founders, expiration of contract, resignation, illness and other provided cases.

Article 11 ‚Äî Academic Council

Permanent body coordinating educational and scientific activities.

Main powers:

- development of development plans;
- making decisions on educational and scientific activities;
- approval of curricula, schedules, disciplines;
- recommendations on personnel issues;
- annual reports of the rector and vice-rectors;
- awarding titles and honors;
- approval of admission rules, internal regulations, specialist training plans;
- participation in formation of the University's educational policy.

Chairman - Rector.
Decisions are made by majority vote.

Article 12 ‚Äî Rector

Manages educational and scientific activities.
Accountable to Founders and President. Appointed by the President in coordination with founders.

Functions:

- organization of educational process;
- implementation of founders' and President's decisions;
- management of Academic Council;
- issuance of orders on educational activities;
- enrollment/expulsion of students;
- hiring teachers and staff;
- approval of heads of scientific subdivisions;
- international representation on agreed issues;
- development of educational regulations;
- resolution of all issues not within competence of President and founders.

Article 13 ‚Äî Vice-Rector

Responsible for educational and upbringing work.

Functions:

- organization of educational and upbringing process;
- work of scientific-methodological council;
- quality control of education;
- coordination of faculties and departments;
- organization of exams, defenses, curricula;
- implementation of new learning technologies;
- professional development of teachers;
- participation in attestations;
- ensuring learning conditions and student welfare;
- reporting, discipline control, fire safety, etc.

Rights:

- represent the university;
- make proposals to the rector;
- receive information from subdivisions.

Responsibility:

- for improper performance of duties;
- for offenses;
- for material damage.

Article 14 ‚Äî Dean of Faculty

Manages educational, scientific and upbringing work of the faculty.
Plans, organizes and controls educational process.
Monitors implementation of curricula of departments and laboratories.

