Summary Article 23 (Research Activities of the University)

The University conducts fundamental and applied research, implements scientific achievements in education, engages in innovation, expertise, analytics and training of scientific-pedagogical staff.
Scientific work is organized through the Research Sector, which includes laboratories, design bureaus and other subdivisions working on contractual basis.
Training of scientific staff is conducted through programs of higher, postgraduate and additional professional education, as well as through attachment of specialists and provision of sabbatical leaves.
The University independently determines scientific directions, develops international cooperation and organizes innovative infrastructure for commercialization of scientific results.
Management of scientific activities is carried out by the Rector and Academic Council.
Intellectual property of the University is protected by law and managed by the University itself.
All issues not regulated by the Charter are regulated by internal normative acts.

Article 24 (Goals and Directions of Scientific Activities)

Main goals of scientific activities - development and optimization of scientific research, formation of priority scientific directions, creation of incentives for scientists, improvement of personnel training quality and integration of science with international educational space.
The University promotes cooperation with organizations and enterprises for solving major scientific-technical tasks and implementing research results in production.

Main directions of work include:
- conducting fundamental and applied research;
- science planning and formation of thematic plans;
- organizational and methodological support of scientific activities;
- creation of scientific subdivisions;
- organization of scientific conferences, forums and exhibitions;
- performance of scientific-technical services and production works;
- participation in grants and targeted programs;
- publication of scientific literature and periodicals;
- development, modernization and supply of scientific-technical products;
- creation of scientific teams, including attraction of external specialists;
- performance of other types of scientific and innovative activities within the law.

section8.content:
Article 27

(Cooperation with Foreign Educational Institutions)

The University has the right to conduct international cooperation in the fields of education, science, culture, sports and other areas of its activities. It is carried out within the framework of Kyrgyzstan's legislation, international agreements and bilateral contracts.

International activities are based on contracts and include interaction with foreign universities, organizations and specialists. Main forms of cooperation:

- participation in exchange programs for pupils, students, postgraduates, doctoral students and teachers;
- training, internships and professional development of University staff abroad;
- joint educational programs, scientific research, conferences, symposiums and other scientific events;
- development and implementation of joint educational programs of all levels, including courses in foreign languages;
- participation in international projects, grants and programs;
- attraction of foreign teachers and specialists, as well as sending own staff to foreign institutions;
- joint scientific, technical, innovative, consulting and analytical activities;
- organization of international conferences and consulting services;
- participation in international organizations and conclusion of cooperation agreements with foreign legal and physical persons.

The University has the right to:
- join international organizations, conclude agreements with foreign partners;
- create branches and representative offices abroad;
- open joint structures with foreign partners (centers, laboratories, technoparks, etc.);
- export and import educational services and scientific-technical products;
- conduct foreign economic activities, conclude transactions domestically and abroad, have its own currency fund.

Funds received from foreign economic activities are not subject to seizure or mandatory taxation if directed to fulfill tasks established by the Law "On Education".
